<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-M4MKw8z-vhmfp6kd035-sg" name="Develop SP,_GGAScIh3EeCE4bK4CwiExg" guid="-M4MKw8z-vhmfp6kd035-sg" changeDate="2011-08-24T03:34:27.506-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The safety plan is a live set of documents that gets refined throughout the safety lifecycle. Because of this a number&#xD;
    of process and documents become part of the safety plan. The documents required to make up the safety plan are detailed&#xD;
    in the safety planning task. The processes required are outlined in this guidance and point to the various clauses in&#xD;
    the ISO 26262 specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The safety manager is responsible for the planning, maintenance and monitoring of&amp;nbsp;the safety activities across the&#xD;
    development sub-phases in the safety lifecycle.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Safety planning should include information relating to the implementation of strategies, activities and the procedures&#xD;
    required for achieving functional safety.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    This covers the planning for all forms of safety based requirements&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;verification and validation&#xD;
    activities, including general planning for confirmation measures.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    The supporting process that are detailed in ISO 26262 Volume 8, such as planning for requirements management,&#xD;
    configuration and change management, interfaces, verification, document templates, the qualification of Software tools,&#xD;
    and hardware and software components.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Detailed guidance is given in ISO 26262 Volume 2, clause 6.4.3.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To plan the functional safety activities required to make the item under development functionally safe&#xD;
    and&amp;nbsp;compliant to ISO 26262.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
